results.name: Jordan Super.Fly MVP PF 'Dark Concord'
results.story: The Jordan Super.Fly debuted in 2012 with a lightweight upper, uniquely ridged midsole, and vents on the upper for breathability. Since then, it’s gone through many iterations, and the Jordan Super.Fly MVP PF 'Dark Concord' represents its evolution. The upper has a mesh base wrapped by a large overlay—minus the vents—made of synthetic material atop a dual-tone React midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG NRG 'Not For Resale' Sample
Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG NRG 'Not For Resale' Sample
Air Jordan 33 'Guo Ailun' PE
results.story: In May 2017, Guo Ailun signed a deal with the Jordan Brand, effectively becoming the first Chinese player to join the fold. The Air Jordan 33 'Guo Ailun' PE is a kids'-sized takedown of the adult shoe that was released in April 2019. To honor Ailun, this rendition includes a white, quilted panel at the tongue and black Chinese characters on the pull tab. This version retains the modern FastFit entry and knit upper of the original AJ33, first seen in 2018.

results.name: Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Paris Saint-Germain' Sample
Air Jordan 1 Retro High GG 'Deadly Pink'
Air Jordan 33 'Future of Flight'
results.story: Jordan Brand brings new technology to the table with the latest signature Air Jordan release. The Air Jordan 33 'Future of Flight' features cutting-edge FastFit technology for a lockdown fit and wide range of motion. Dressed in white, the sneaker also sports a mesh upper with black accents on the forefoot side, oversized tongue and heel, and on the collar lining. For a pop of color, the sneaker showcases red details on the elastic eyelets and a translucent outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid GS 'Pure Platinum'
Air Jordan 7 Retro Low NRG 'Bordeaux'
results.story: Paying tribute to the original colorway of the Bordeaux Air Jordan 7s, Nike released a low-top version in this fall 2018 update. The Air Jordan 7 Retro Low NRG 'Bordeaux' features a Light Graphite nubuck upper with black nubuck overlays and perforations along the midfoot for breathability. Design touches include the multicolor geometric patterns on the inner neoprene bootie and outsole, the ‘23’ shield logo at the heel, Bordeaux accents on the throat and jeweled black accents on the midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro Low NRG 'Taxi'
results.story: September 2018 saw Jordan Brand drop three colorways of the Air Jordan 7 Retro Low: one in Concord, another in Bordeaux and, in the case of this yellow model, the third in Taxi. Unlike previous iterations of the AJ7, which favored colorful geometric patterns, this design delivers a clean Taxi yellow across the leather upper and neoprene inner sleeve. Contrast can be found on the sole, where bright shapes share space with a green Jumpman logo.

Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Pine Green' Sample
Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Court Purple' Sample
Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Black Cone'
results.story: Drawing inspiration from the original, the Air Jordan 1 Mid PS sneaker puts a modern spin on the sneaker that started an on-court sensation back in 1985. This 'Black Cone' kids' iteration—debuted in September 2018—continues the legacy in a color block leather upper with a nylon tongue, a heel tab and lace closure. A debossed Wings logo and Swooshes add a time-honored element. The two-tone Air-Sole mimics the adult platform.

Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid GS 'Bordeaux'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid GS 'Bordeaux' dresses an updated version of Michael Jordan's iconic first signature sneaker with a two-tone colorway. Bordeaux covers its premium upper, which stays true to the 1985 OG. Released in August 2018, the kids' shoe displays the Jumpman logo on the tongue and heel, the Wings logo near the ankle and the Nike Swoosh on the quarter panel. Sail coats the midsole and outsole, the latter which possesses a pivot point tread pattern to help with traction.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid TD 'Gym Red'
Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Friends & Family'
Jordan CP3.XI 'Dallas Cowboys'
results.story: Released in August 2018, in the lead-up to football season, the Jordan CP3.XI ‘Dallas Cowboys’ celebrates Chris Paul’s favorite NFL team. The performance basketball shoe is dressed in the official colors of the NFL franchise also known as ‘America’s Team.’ A sculpted grey suede upper is accented with an adjustable midfoot strap finished in navy blue and white stripes, along with a small silver Jumpman.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 Low PF 'Cement'
results.story: Russell Westbrook’s signature Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 PF reworks Nike’s iconic Cement color palette, which appears on the upper as well as the midsole. The greyscale design forgoes the usual forefoot strap, while the aesthetic itself features a lower cut than the original. The shoe also sports a toggle lacing system and an inner bootie design.

results.name: Air Jordan 4 'Florida Gators' PE
results.story: The Air Jordan 4 'Florida Gators' PE is a rare, player exclusive edition provided to the University of Florida's football team in 2018 as it prepared to face the Michigan Wolverines in the Peach Bowl. It presents the iconic AJ4—first seen in 1989 and designed by Tinker Hatfield—with a blue suede upper and the Gators logo on the tongue. The sneaker features the Jumpman in orange on the heel, clear wings with a paint splatter design and an icy blue outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High BG 'Red Black'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High BG 'Red Black' reintroduces an iconic silhouette with colors that are familiar to the sneaker. Released in 2016, this shoe's colorway of Gym Red, black and white are similar to the Chicago Bulls' colors that inspired the first AJ1 that debuted in 1985. Like the OG, this shoe comes with Jordan branding, a leather upper that promotes comfort, and cushioning to help maintain support on and off the court.

results.name: Wmns Air Jordan 1 Rebel XX 'Light Cream'
Wmns Air Jordan 1 Rebel XX 'Olive Canvas' Sample
Jordan Trainer 3 'UNC Tar Heels'
results.story: Released as part of a ‘Week Zero’ pack celebrating four NCAA football teams, the UNC Tar Heels’ Jordan Trainer 3 features official school and mascot branding on the heels, insoles, and midfoot straps which read ‘TAR’ and ‘HEELS.’ Team colors of Carolina Blue and white are highlighted throughout the jersey mesh construction.

results.name: Jordan Trainer 3 'Florida Gators'
results.story: The Jordan Trainer 3 ‘Florida Gators’ pays tribute to the college football powerhouse through a two-tone colorway inspired by the school’s official colors. The mesh upper is finished in Game Royal with University Orange accents to create a subtle gradient effect, while the adjustable midfoot straps are separately emblazoned with ‘Florida’ and ‘Gators.’ Similarly, the heel panels are individually marked – one with a Jumpman logo, the other with a solitary ‘F.’

results.name: Jordan Trainer 3 'Michigan Wolverines'
results.story: This Jordan Trainer 3 appears in University of Michigan colors with team branding throughout, while technical components, like Nike Zoom cushioning and Flightspeed, are designed for a high-energy response. Lightweight mesh applications on the upper maximize breathability, while the midfoot straps promote stability. The words ‘GO’ and ‘BLUE’ are written across the straps, while the heels are accented with Jumpman and ‘M’ logos to round out the collegiate look.

results.name: Jordan Trainer 3 'Oklahoma Sooners'
results.story: After joining the Jordan Brand in 2017, this Oklahoma Sooners team-based colorway was released in June 2018 as part of a Jordan Trainer 3 pack consisting of four NCAA football teams. The Trainer 3’s jersey mesh construction is complimented by official school and mascot branding on the heels, insoles, and midfoot straps which read ‘BOOMER’ and ‘SOONER.’

results.name: Jordan CP3.XI 'Cliff Paul'
results.story: Nike pays tribute to Chris Paul’s twin brother Cliff, known for his State Farm commercials, with the Jordan CP3.XI ‘Cliff Paul’ iteration released for summer 2018. A nod to Cliff’s knack for khakis and plaid sweaters, the design is dressed in a Desert Sand, white, University Red, and metallic gold color scheme that comes together at the tongue and laces. Other details include gold Jumpman branding, a white midsole, and an icy translucent outsole.

Air Jordan 9 Retro Boot 'University of Florida' PE
results.story: In anticipation of the SEC kickoff in July 2018, the Jordan brand unveiled their partnership with the University of Florida. This Air Jordan 9 Retro Boot showcases school pride with Gator inspired details while upgrading the silhouette with a durable, weather resistant textile upper and rugged outsole. This exclusive version highlights the school's orange and black colorway and adds a blue Jumpman on the outsole for a burst of color.

results.name: Wmns Air Jordan 1 Retro High Zip 'Particle Beige' Sample
Air Jordan Spiz'ike BG 'Midnight Navy'
results.story: As one of the many re-releases of the 2006 Spizike, the updated AJ Spizike in 'Midnight Navy' was released in September 2017. The Air Jordan Spizike BG takes elements from the adult-released sneaker and inserts them into a kids'-sized version. Rocking a synthetic and leather upper, the shoe features AJ lacing wings with an adjustable toggle closure. Underfoot, the Air cushioning provides comfort to growing feet.

results.name: Air Jordan 32 'Finale'
results.story: The Air Jordan 32 takes a bow with this ‘Finale’ colorway from July 2018, featuring a Flyknit upper crafted from a combination of blue, red and purple yarns. The intricate multicolor finish is balanced by black laces directly integrated into the knit structure, along with a crisp white heel counter that blends into the midsole. Finally, the mid-top is adorned with unique badging in the form of a large Jordan ‘Wings’ logo on the heel and ‘Finale’ woven label on the interior of the tongue.

results.name: Jordan Future GS 'Quai 54'
results.story: Every year, Jordan Brand’s Quai 54 streetball competition acts as the design inspiration for an annual footwear collection. The June 2018 release included this Jordan Future GS 'Quai 54,’ featuring a black woven upper accented with the tournament’s signature colors. A broad pink stripe runs down the side, bright green covers the heel, and vibrant blue wraps around the base of the forefoot. The Air Jordan 11-inspired tooling is crafted with a black midsole and translucent blue outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 32 Low PF 'Last Shot'
results.story: The Air Jordan 32 Low PF ‘Last Shot’ sneaker pays homage to the legendary last shot that Michael Jordan took in Game 6 of the 1998 Finals, celebrating the huge win for the city of Chicago. The Black and Gym Red colorway honor the Chicago Bulls, with shiny red Jumpman branding and a sleek red outsole. An oversized Air Jordan Wings logo is imprinted into the heel, symbolic of Michael Jordan leaving his mark on the game.

results.name: Off-White x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'UNC'
results.story: Inspired by Michael Jordan’s alma mater, the Off-White x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘UNC’ carries a classic two-tone composition, filtered through Virgil Abloh’s unique design prism. The process involves taking a white leather base with dark powder blue overlays and adding embellishments that convey an expressive, handmade quality. They include detached Wings, a floating Swoosh, and lines of text on the medial-side quarter panel delineating the taxonomy of the shoe.

results.name: Off-White x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'UNC' Sample
Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 'Noah'
results.story: This iteration of Russell Westbrook’s signature shoe celebrates a very unique milestone — the first birthday of his son, Noah. Dressed in black and white with emerald highlights, The Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 'Noah' features a mesh construction for a lightweight, locked-in feel. Along with Westbrook’s own branding, Noah’s date of birth — 5.16.17 — is printed on the inside of the strap.

results.name: Air Jordan 32 Low 'Gordon St.'
results.story: For the Air Jordan 32 Low ‘Gordon St.’, Jordan brand delved into Michael Jordan’s personal history and named the shoe after the street he grew up on. The ‘Gordon St.’ is outfitted in a tan colorway with hits of red near the ankle and tongue. The Gordon St sign, stitched on the inside tongue, brings it all home.

results.name: Air Jordan Standard
results.story: Belying its straightforward name, the Air Jordan Standard isn’t made for basketball. It’s a lifestyle running shoe, finished here in a triple-white colorway that showcases the shoe’s various textures. They include a feathered leather upper, a spacer-mesh collar and a stretch midfoot strap covered in tonal elephant print. It’s all mounted on a midsole inspired by the Nike Sock Dart.

results.name: Air Jordan Standard
results.story: The Air Jordan Standard is a lifestyle running shoe that blends old and new, finished in a triple-black colorway that highlights details from past Jordan and Nike models. The tooling is borrowed from the Nike Sock Dart, while the stretch midfoot strap is embossed with a distinctive texture that recalls the elephant print of the Air Jordan 3. A contemporary aesthetic is delivered by the use of a feathered leather upper.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Blue Moon' Sample
Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid BT 'Crayon Pack'
results.story: Inspired by the original Air Jordan, the Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid BT 'Crayon Pack' sneaker is a kid’s version of the iconic Michael Jordan shoe from 1985. Sporting many of the same specs as the adult version, this shoe features an all-leather upper in a black and white motif. A hit of blue accents the Swoosh, while a rubber outsole completes this classic design.

results.name: Jordan 6 Rings PS 'Space Jam'
results.story: This take on the Jordan 6 Rings comes with a Space Jam-inspired colorway of black, Hyper Royal and white. The kids' shoe, a sized-down version of the adult model from 2018, features elements from the Air Jordan 6, 7, 8, 11, 12, 13 and 14—models that were worn by MJ during his six championship runs. The sneaker comes with an abundance of Jordan branding, a premium upper and a shiny mudguard. Finishing the style is a foam midsole and durable rubber outsole, both in white.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Game Royal' Sample
Colette x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Au Revoir'
Air Jordan 32 Low PF 'Michigan Wolverines'
results.story: As part of their March Madness collection, Jordan Brand has released a Michigan Wolverines-inspired model just in time for the 2018 NCAA tournament. The Air Jordan 32 Low 'Michigan Wolverines' features a Flyknit upper in College Navy with yellow accents interwoven throughout, a marbled grey midsole with a Jumpman logo, a Maize rubber outsole, and graphics of a pair of scissors cutting down a basketball net on the inner tongues. Additional features include Michigan branding on the insoles and inner and outer tongues that read “Go Blue.”

Air Jordan 13 Retro GT 'City of Flight'
Steve Harrington x Air Jordan 1 Retro High Custom 'Makers Studio'
results.story: Californian pop artist Steve Harrington teamed up with Nike to release a unique colorway showcasing his pop-art. The Steve Harrington x Air Jordan 1 Retro High Custom 'Makers Studio' is part of a collection of matching apparel and features an all-white leather upper with perforations along the outsole and toe box and a unique Swoosh design.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 'City of Flight'
results.story: To pay tribute to his hometown, Russell Westbrook designed a new edition of his signature Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 silhouette. The Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 'City of Flight' features a black canvas upper with a white map of Los Angeles printed all over the shoe. The sneaker also features a thick color-blocked midsole and heel, and a wraparound elastic band with black and white "LA" and "RW" lettering on the left and right tongues.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid BP 'Crayon Pack'
results.story: The Michael Jordan sneaker that started it all returns in a kids’ edition—the Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid BP sneaker sports a classic color block scheme on an all-leather upper. As the only Air Jordan model to sport prominent Nike branding, this kids’ version of the Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid dresses its Swoosh in Hyper Cobalt for a hit of color on its black and white build. A durable rubber outsole underfoot complements the design.

results.name: Wmns Air Jordan 1 Lover XX 'The 1 Reimagined' Sample
Jordan Pro Strong 'Racer Pink'
results.story: Released in January 2019, the Jordan Pro Strong 'Racer Pink' is a high-top sneaker with a leather and synthetic upper and prominent Jordan branding on the tongue and heel. Presented with a colorway of Sail, Racer Pink and Racer Blue, the shoe is an updated take on a model first seen in 1998. It features a heel pull tab, hidden ghillie lacing system, compression-molded Phylon cushioning and a rubber outsole with a herringbone traction pattern.

results.name: Air Jordan 23 Low PF 'Free Throw Line'
Air Jordan 13 Retro PS 'Olive'
results.story: The Jordan 13 Retro PS sneaker is a kids'-size edition of the AJ13, originally released in 1997 and inspired by Michael Jordan's 'Black Cat' nickname. Sneaker designer Tinker Hatfield took the nickname literally, looking to a puma's paws when sketching the shape of its sole. This version boasts a black suede upper, with multiple Gym Red branding hits and a classic holographic 'eye' at the heel.

results.name: Air Jordan 13 Retro TD 'Olive'
results.story: The Air Jordan 13 Retro TD ‘Olive’ sneaker updates the original design in a black and light olive colorway with suede overlays in this kids’ version of the iconic silhouette. Tinker Hatfield’s Air Jordan 13 originally released in 1997, influenced by MJ’s ‘Black Cat' nickname. Featuring a leather and textile upper, the Retro TD iteration incorporates an ‘eye’ hologram at the heel to mimic a panther’s eye and a curved outsole inspired by a panther’s paw.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 '2-Way'
results.story: The ‘2-Way' was the global launch colorway for Russell Westbrook’s first signature shoe, the Jordan Why Not Zer0.1. The sleek black and white look comes with a fused-mesh upper, smooth vamp cover, a hook-and-loop strap, and a front toggle. It also has a full-length Zoom Air unit and a durable rubber outsole. The sneaker dropped in February 2018 after the limited January 2018 release of the PE Jordan Why Not Zer0.1 ‘Mirror Image.’
